reviews.text:
This is a wonderfully balanced floral recipe and I think one that will be a great introduction to florals for those who don't venture in to that genre often. The main note here is the Pink Guava handling the show with it's bright, citrusy, slightly funky flavor with some lovely floral accents with the sweet elderflower, bright lychee, and subtle honeysuckle, all being complimented by a creamy mild coconut. &#xD;
&#xD;
It's wonderfully refreshing and the floral notes are bright and pleasant and in no way obtrusive or distracting, making for an easy ADV. One of Kopel's greatest skills IMO is balance and this recipe sure as shoot does not disappoint.
